<span id="freeTextContainer12753864256918463693">I have always been a fan of Chomsky, anyone who is close to me understands that I have secretly forced Noam to marry me. <br/><br/>However. <br/><br/>I cannot help but believe this book has been so very forced, this 100 paged book doesn&apos;t tell us anything we don&apos;t really know. Just gives the typical anarchist bull, but it doesn&apos;t really go into great depths on HOW the media is controlled, WHO it is controlled by and WHY has it been set up this way. nor does it tell us why we&apos;re so easily convinced. <br/><br/>furthermore I am</span>
  <span id="freeText12753864256918463693" style="display:none">I have always been a fan of Chomsky, anyone who is close to me understands that I have secretly forced Noam to marry me. <br /><br />However. <br /><br />I cannot help but believe this book has been so very forced, this 100 paged book doesn't tell us anything we don't really know. Just gives the typical anarchist bull, but it doesn't really go into great depths on HOW the media is controlled, WHO it is controlled by and WHY has it been set up this way. nor does it tell us why we're so easily convinced. <br /><br />furthermore I am unimpressed by the academic elitist bile which is set up when he refers to people as the "bewildered herd" who just want to watch reality shows. people are not so stupid, they understand if they are given the sources. <br /><br />still love you noam, but boo. </span>
